    "created_at": "2023-12-14T15:30:18Z",
    "updated_at": "2023-12-14T15:30:18Z",
    "body": "If you set the `AWS_PROFILE` env var  (e.g. in .bashrc/.zshrc or via direnv per directory), you can then use all aws related commands without specifying a `--profile`. This env var is then used by both `aws sso login` and any other `aws`command (e.g. `aws s3` or `cdk deploy`). So I think you have to change your workflow from specifying the `--profile` in each call to exporting the env var in your session and starship should then also pick that information up.",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "pin": null,
